				<main class=""><article class="main-content-home"><h1 class="">Welcome to Riverside</h1>
        <p class="">Riverside School District #2 is located in Phoenix, Arizona. Our district is made up of newer residential properties with nearly 1,000 students on our three campuses. We are very fortunate to have the advantage of commercial, university, and industrial partnerships that help support our advanced curriculum, state-of-the-art sports facilities, year-round extracurricular activities, fully funded after-school academic tutoring programs, and integrated instructional technologies that are unavailable to many large and private schools. In essence, we are the school district of choice for the discerning parent. </p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">We are excited for parents, students, and the community to become part of the Riverside family—a community school district where students are provided with an advanced curriculum by master teachers and highly qualified staff. We invite you to use our district website to learn more about our wonderful programs, our state-of-the-art schools, and our many academic achievements. For information about becoming part of the Riverside School District faculty and staff, visit our <a href="/Human-Resources" title="" alt="" target="_self">Human Resources Department</a> page. To take part in donating directly to our student extra-curricular programs, please visit our <a href="/School-Tax-Credits" title="" alt="" target="_self">School Tax Credits</a> page to facilitate your contribution. Please take the time to review the <a href="/Calendar" title="" alt="" target="_self" class="">current district school calendar</a> so you can schedule your volunteer time at one of our schools. If you have any questions or comments, we hope you will feel free to <a href="/Contact-Us" title="" alt="" target="_self">contact us</a> directly.</p>
